will go like this.

01:50.210 --> 01:52.474
First, I'll be introduced...

01:52.613 --> 01:54.445
You know where
he threw it today?

01:54.581 --> 01:56.049
On the porch. On the porch.

01:56.183 --> 01:57.344
- On the porch.
- Well...

01:57.484 --> 01:59.213
Took me ten minutes
before I found it.

01:59.353 --> 02:00.582
I almost froze to death.

02:00.721 --> 02:03.190
Well, he's supposed to throw it
on the porch, dear.

02:03.323 --> 02:05.121
Well, it's the first time
in two years, Marion.

02:05.258 --> 02:06.191
Dad. Uh, Mom?

02:06.326 --> 02:08.351
Well, everybody has an off day.

02:08.495 --> 02:09.985
Yeah, when I delivered
papers as a kid,

02:10.130 --> 02:11.427
- I always hit the porch.
- Dad! Mom?

02:11.565 --> 02:13.055
Richard, there's
no need to shout.

02:13.200 --> 02:16.033
Oh, Howard, Richard has his
great sophomore debate today.

02:16.169 --> 02:17.193
Yeah.

02:17.337 --> 02:18.668
Let me give you
some advice, Richard.

02:18.805 --> 02:20.170
Oh, good. I need some.

02:20.307 --> 02:21.968
- Shave.
- Shave?

02:22.109 --> 02:24.009
Must have cost Nixon
a million votes.

02:24.144 --> 02:26.238
You thought he won that debate.

02:26.380 --> 02:28.075
Well, he did.
That's the point.

02:28.215 --> 02:30.343
He did.
He scored very well.

02:30.484 --> 02:33.317
But the next day, all I heard
was: "Nixon didn't shave."

02:33.453 --> 02:35.012
Well, he looked a little scuff y.

02:35.155 --> 02:36.350
Yeah. Boy, did he.

02:36.490 --> 02:38.754
All right, now,
about my campaign...

02:38.892 --> 02:40.189
-(Joanie groaning)
-(Richie groans)

02:40.327 --> 02:42.694
Oh, Mom, I feel really sick.

02:42.829 --> 02:43.990
Feel my forehead.

02:44.131 --> 02:47.157
Oh, Joanie, you cannot stay home
from school today.

02:47.300 --> 02:49.200
Oh, Mom, I'm sure it's the flu.

02:50.237 --> 02:52.035
A virus--
you know, that's worse.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.504
Malaria.

02:54.641 --> 02:58.202
<i>Joanie, a“ you have
